    %h5 The Innovation School Model
    %p
      The Innovation Schools initiative was signed into law in January 2010.
      It allows districts to to explore innovative ideas while keeping school funding within districts.
    %p
      It requires that the Superintendent, Teacher's Union (Cambridge Education Association),
      and the School Committee all have a voice in the planning process and a vote in the approval proccess.
    %p
      There are currently 50 innovations schools around Massachusetts including 7 in Boston.
    %p
      There are not yet any innovation schools in Cambridge.

